================================================================================
Data and content notice (NOT covered by the MIT license above):

This project bundles or links to public data and reporting from third parties.
Each source retains its own license / terms of use:

  - Satellite imagery: Esri World Imagery / Wayback (Esri terms)
  - Base map / building data: OpenStreetMap contributors (ODbL); Microsoft
    Building Footprints (ODbL-equivalent)
  - Boundary / reference tiles: Esri (Esri terms)
  - Sanctions data: U.S. Treasury OFAC SDN list (public domain)
  - Location images in images/: Wikimedia Commons, with per-file CC license
    recorded in the image_resource table
  - News article preview images shown by the event viewer: hot-linked from each
    publisher's og:image. Copyright remains with the original publishers; the
    viewer surfaces them via link only, with attribution and a source URL.
  - Narration / event summaries / testimony / daily-life snippets: editorial
    text written by the project, grounded in public reporting, with source URLs
    recorded in the database.

Human-trafficking victim testimony is shown anonymized (nationality / role /
age only; any names are pseudonyms used by the original outlets).

This project is intended for defensive / educational OSINT visualization. Do
not use it to identify, target, or contact specific individuals.
